values:
Family sucks. Things with my family are not good. As I'm typing these first lines I'm vowing to myself to keep this short because I don't really want to get into it,&nbsp;I just want to say a few things.&nbsp;

My mother is a blind idiot who doesn't know how to handle anything. She's desperate for "a relationship" with me when all I really want is for her to leave me alone. Because she pushes things. To ridiculous breaking points and she doesn't realize and is probably incapable of realizing how to grow up.&nbsp;

My dad hates me. He's silent about it but he gives me looks and carries a "fuck you" attitude on&nbsp;his shoulders whenever he's around me. I'm pretty sure he blames me for everything. I'm a "little bitch", which he's told me to my face on more than one occassion but for the most part he just ignores me. Which is better, I'm pretty sure, than following me around the house like my mother does.&nbsp;

My mother seriously does not leave me alone when I'm home. She will follow me and try to start "conversations" with me. She wants to know what "she ever did wrong" but honestly, I can't even tell you how often&nbsp;I have tried to have this conversation with her. It always gets absolutely nowhere because she's too damn blind for it to matter. She doesn't really listen to a word I say. EVER.

So I'm done, basically. Done trying.&nbsp;

Eh, it was short enough.

Goddamn. Living is expensive. On top of gas prices and paying 40 bucks a month for insurance, which I'm sure is actually relatively cheap, it's the holidays. And holidays mean you have to give presents. Presents cost money. I don't care what people say, realistically, presents cost money. Money I don't have.

This colonial writers english test is stressing me out. I'm so sick of all of it. I haven't studied much compared to others and yet I want to curl in a ball everytime I look at the stack of papers. We were supposed to have the test Monday, but that was an ice day, so no school. Today we did some career/college thing the counsellors scheduled. So it's been put off two days and I just want it to be over.&nbsp;

I got a 76 on our last math test. Nobody did well on it all except one kid who is a genius anyways. It's frustrating because when the teacher "teaches" she talks to him only. It's like they're having a one-on-one session. He gets all the answers faster than anyone else, so she just goes with what he says, paying on attention to the fact that nobody else in the class understands what's going on. I'm not blaming my grade on the teacher, but she hasn't exactly been helping.&nbsp;

Synergy is difficult. I'm exhausted. It's after 10 now. So I'm going to go to bed soon, hopefully. I&nbsp;have studied some for english, but I am not going to obsess about it. I learned a while ago that hardcore stressing and freaking and&nbsp;cramming&nbsp;isn't going to help me any.&nbsp; But after two extra unexpected nights to study it has sort of gotten to the point where I no excuses. I had better get a good grade on this. I don't enjoy what we're doing currently, so that makes it even harder to focus. I am loving chem though. And when I have chem homework I do that first and longer and with more concentration than the rest. And it is showing in my grades. Ugh.

&nbsp;I just need a place to jot down some thoughts I'm having right now. 
Potentially, these thoughts are life changing, at the very least kind of uplifting. 

One of my best friends mom died of cancer this past weekend 
I went to her memorial service today and it was a really nice celebration of her life, as they called it.&nbsp;
This woman was described as living life to the fullest, the kind of person who really touched people and who really got all she could out of life. From what I know about her and from when I've talked to her, this is all so&nbsp;true.&nbsp; 
She seemed to be really an amazing, strong person with strong faith.&nbsp; 
This is the kind of person I want to be. I want to live my life as fully as possible and with faith like that.&nbsp; 
Really, I was truly affected. 
I swear, however wackily spiritual this may sound, I looked outside at one point and the wind was blowing the leaves on the trees and I swear I saw her in them.&nbsp;

Well, hello.&nbsp;

The recruiting camp today went pretty well, I guess. I didn't do amazing or anything, but I guess I didn't completely suck. So we'll see. There are so many rules and things to know for the recruiting process. It's ridiculously complicated. Oh well, we'll get through it I guess.

Tomorrow we have four games(!!!). Holy crap that is a lot. I'm excited though to try to make that whole not thinking thing work. Hopefully permanently. Really, mindframes are so important. In basically everything you do.

I'm working on getting those pictures up... I didn't go to my brother's game tonight, so I was actually able to stay home alone. Uploading is slow going, though, because I can't download any of the tools that are supposed to make it go faster because I really really doubt my parents would let me have a flickr account if they knew about. Seriously, I'm not even allowed to have instant messaging. No joke.&nbsp;

Ah well. College will end the sneaking, I suppose. At least to a certain extent. Two more years. More like one and half?&nbsp;

Anyway, they're home, I'm out.

Congrats to Polanco, Ordonez, and Pudge for earning an All Star start and Carlos and Verlander for reserves... that's awesome to see the love for Tigers. One final vote remains... Jeremy Bonderman is up for the final vote, so we're definitely voting for him as many times as possible.&nbsp;

I consider myself a baseball purist. Old school, if you will.&nbsp;I would so much rather see a pitching duel than a slugfest. I think triples are way more exciting (okay, only in most cases) than homeruns. I love speed and basestealers.&nbsp;
This is why last night's Tigers/Twins game thoroughly excited me. Score tied at nothing going into&nbsp;the bottom of the eighth. Bondo (VOTE VOTE VOTE!!!!) was pitching spectacularly and his counterpart, Baker, was pitching just as well. Marcus Thames, who is one of those guys you just have to root for, started at DH for Sheff who was serving a suspension, hits a line drive homerun and Jonesy closes it out in the ninth one-two-three. Beautiful.

Next topic. I have a job now. Today was the second day.&nbsp;It's at the same place my mom works, which can get kind of sticky at times, but it's extremely convenient. It's good pay, but it's been frustrating because nobody seems to know what they want me to do with what they hired me to do. It's just really frustrating because sometimes I feel like I'm more just in the way than anything or I'm kind of useless. I sometimes feel like I'm getting paid (more than minimum(!)) to just sit there and take up space. Oh well,&nbsp;I guess I kind of can't complain too much. I mean, I AM getting paid (more than minimum).&nbsp;I guess.&nbsp;

When I actually get sleep, I dream. My dreams are never good ones. They almost always leave me with an uneasy, disturbed feeling when I wake up. Sometimes I don't even remember what I dream about, but there's still that nagging feeling. It's like a sinking feeling. Like when you go to sleep to try to sleep off something bad, like a bad day or something, but when you wake up you know that something is wrong, but you can't quite think of what it is. It's&nbsp;kind of&nbsp;depressing.

Well, it's almost 10 now, so I'm going to try to get some sleep.&nbsp;The working all day thing is extremely exhausting, even when it feels like I'm not doing anything. Especially when it feels like I'm not doing anything.&nbsp;
